{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Cherry Syrup","content":["Place cherries, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>6 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>, then blend <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr> <strong>-10,<\/strong> <strong>increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 10.<\/strong> Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Meringues","content":["Preheat oven to 150°C. Line 3 large baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place sugars into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into a separate bowl and set aside. Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>4-6 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr> <strong>,<\/strong> <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>, until very stiff peaks form.","Mix <nobr>4 min\/37°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, slowly adding reserved sugar (1 teaspoon at a time), vinegar and vanilla through hole in mixing bowl lid. Mixture should be glossy and smooth. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Divide meringue mixture evenly between 3 bowls. Add 2 tablespoons of the reserved cherry syrup to 1 bowl and gently combine using a metal spoon, taking care not to remove air from mixture. Add cocoa powder to another bowl, and gently swirl through to create a marbled effect. Do not add anything to last bowl of eggwhites.","Using a piping bag with a round nozzle (1 cm), pipe each mixture into approx. 30 small circles (approx. 4 cm in diameter) onto the prepared trays. Using a fine-mesh sieve, dust cherry meringues with freeze-dried cherry powder (optional) and dust chocolate meringues with extra cocoa powder. Place trays into oven, reduce temperature to 110°C and bake for 1 hour (110°C). Turn off oven and leave meringues to cool completely with oven door shut (approx. 2 hours). Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":[" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>45 sec\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>, or until soft peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Using 2-3 serving platters or cake stands (approx. 30 cm diameter), dot whipped cream onto platters in a circular pattern and arrange meringues, alternating flavours, on top of cream (using cream to secure meringues). Build pavlova towers by dotting cream onto meringues and stacking meringues in a vertical circular pattern. Fill any gaps between meringues with whipped cream, berries and mint leaves. Serve with extra cherries and cherry syrup. "]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Cherry Syrup","content":["250 g fresh pitted cherries, plus extra to serve","50 g caster sugar","20 g lemon juice","½ tsp ground cinnamon"]},{"title":"Meringues","content":["270 g white sugar","60 g brown sugar","8 egg whites, room temperature","½ tsp cream of tartar","1 tsp white vinegar","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 tbsp cocoa powder, sifted, plus extra for dusting","2 tsp freeze-dried cherry powder (optional - see Tips)"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["800 g thickened cream","500 g fresh mixed berries","4 sprigs fresh mint leaves"]}],"id":"r119777","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-JdatEgGwhQo\/XZWdz9rUvrI\/AAAAAAAAeqg\/s1lcps0mRLwD4xJZuWPv0HwNrhiMZbsvwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_MnTfTStZv58dKolu.png","title":"Pavlova towers","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.6 g","fat":"37.7 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"57.3 g","calories":"2473 kJ \/ 588 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, baking paper, 3 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), 3 bowls, fine mesh sieve, piping bag with round nozzle (1 cm), 3 serving platters, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Frozen, thawed cherries can be used when fresh are not available.","Freeze-dried fruit powders can be found at some health food stores.","All components (including meringues and whipped cream) can be placed into sealed containers and assembled just before serving."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","4h 30m","8 portions"]}